Thanks Paul, and everybody else who replied, either on the list or via
pmail.  Got some really good advice and confirmed what I had guessed,
which was that the bored 1600 would not be a practical replacement.  My
friend was trying to save me some money but was not familiar with the
difference between Type 1 and Type 4 engines.  I think I'm going to
shell out the cash for a rebuilt stock Type 4 2000cc - sounds like the
hassle avoided will be well worth the extra $$.

In the meantime, looks like I'll be ordering a swing lever pin kit and a
new set of ball joints or rebuilt torsion arms.  This should be fun! :)

